        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 10:27PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1027 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Busby, or 25 miles southwest of Colstrip, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colstrip, Busby, Northern Cheyenne Indian Reservation and Crow
Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
